      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match COU operating envelope (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) within specified tolerances; full uncertainty characterisation of test rig boundary conditions required.",
      "rationale": "Bench experiments used bovine blood with variable hematocrit; temperature and viscosity were not controlled to clinical VAD tolerances. Boundary condition uncertainty propagation into test data was not quantified. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E_rel or validation uncertainty) must be computed for hemolysis index at all 5 COU operating points with combined simulation and experimental uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Relative error computed at 3 of 5 operating points; 2 points lacked sufficient experimental replication for statistical comparison. Combined validation uncertainty not formally propagated. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The validation QoI (hemolysis index) must be directly and traceably linked to the COU decision QoI (absolute clinical hemolysis threshold); surrogate metrics are not acceptable at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index used in validation is the Normalized Index of Hemolysis (NIH), which maps directly to clinical threshold. Linkage is documented but conversion uncertainty between NIH and plasma free haemoglobin was not fully characterised. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
