      "acceptanceCriteria": "Evidence that simulation setup, boundary condition assignment, and post-processing were reviewed by an independent analyst; documented checklist required.",
      "rationale": "No independent review of simulation setup was performed. A single analyst configured all five operating-point cases. Use error assessment not conducted; flagged as epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification for selection of turbulence closure and hemolysis damage model form must be supported by sensitivity analysis and literature evidence specific to high-shear rotary blood pump flows.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected without sensitivity comparison to RSM or LES for rotating frame hemolysis prediction. Power-law damage model exponents taken from literature without re-calibration to pump geometry. Model form uncertainty not quantified. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters (fluid properties, damage model constants, boundary conditions) must have documented uncertainty distributions; Monte Carlo propagation must cover full COU operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed on three of nine input parameters; blood viscosity, surface roughness, and damage model exponents were treated as deterministic. Partial UQ coverage insufficient for MRL 5 absolute prediction. Achieved level 2."
    },
